PN,46110
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F461A1773929472
OL,3,CWelsh NHS came 'close to collapse' and
OL,4,Cdoctors had 'no PPE', inquiry finds
OL,6,FThe First Minister, Eluned Morgan
OL,7,Fsaid, "The pandemic placed significant
OL,8,Fpressures on health and care services
OL,9,Fin Wales and across the UK. We
OL,10,Facknowledge the considerable impact
OL,11,Fthis had on patients, staff, the wider
OL,12,Fworkforce and families affected by
OL,13,FCovid-19.
OL,15,FThe Welsh Government continues to
OL,16,Fengage with the inquiry in an open and
OL,17,Fconstructive manner, as we have done
OL,18,Fin relation to the first two reports.
OL,19,FThe inquiry requires a response to the
OL,20,FModule 3 report and recommendations
OL,21,Fwithin six months of publication."
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G10/13
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
